stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> FREE
    FREE --> REQUESTED: build MdlRequest
    REQUESTED --> PRE_ACQUIRE_NOTIFY: notify storage engine
    PRE_ACQUIRE_NOTIFY --> GRANTED: compatible
    PRE_ACQUIRE_NOTIFY --> PENDING: conflict
    PENDING --> GRANTED: blockers released
    PENDING --> VICTIM: MDL deadlock detector
    PENDING --> TIMEOUT: lock wait timeout
    PENDING --> KILLED: session killed
    GRANTED --> POST_RELEASE_NOTIFY: release by statement or transaction
    POST_RELEASE_NOTIFY --> RELEASED: notify complete
    VICTIM --> RELEASED: cleanup pending request
    TIMEOUT --> RELEASED: cleanup pending request
    KILLED --> RELEASED: cleanup pending request
    RELEASED --> FREE
    FREE --> [*]

    note right of PENDING
        MDL waits are metadata waits.
        They do not hold Buffer Pool page latch,
        file latch, MTR latch, or row-lock shard lock.
    end note

    note right of GRANTED
        Ownership is Session or statement scope.
        DDL EXCLUSIVE locks normally survive until DDL end.
    end note

